<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-06-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 551/42.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-19"><hi rend="italic">June 19,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Rockhill states that he has been officially informed by the foreign
                            office that the customs-houses will be opened on July 1, at Dairen and
                            Antung, with a branch house at Tatungkou.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>